    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-06T11:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-06T11:44:00-05:00" n="749"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79682/68: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-06T16:00:00-00:44"
                            >January 6, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 21—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–1. Referring to the Department’s airgram A–35, November 27, 1943, 6:30 p.m.,
                    the Liberian Government would not be unfavorable to according Pan American
                    Airways exemptions of taxation with respect to all materials, supplies and
                    equipment for the construction, use and operation of airports of the United
                    States for the duration of the war and 6 months thereafter. However, the
                    Liberian Government does not see its way clear to grant exemptions of taxation
                    on materials and supplies imported into Liberia for the personal use of civilian
                    personnel and the families of Pan American Airways.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
